<TEXT>&#2;<DATELINE>2016-12-31</DATELINE><TITLE>Chapter 13 Economic and Political Impact of Ebola Virus Disease</TITLE><BODY>We are at a dangerous moment in these three West African countries, all fragile states that have had strong economic growth in recent years after decades of wars and poor governance. It would be scandalous to let this crisis escalate further when we have the knowledge, tools, and resources to stop it. Tens of thousands of lives, the future of the region, and hard-won economic and health gains for millions hang in the balance. Jim Yong Kim and Paul Farmer, World Bank Group President and Harvard University Professor, The Washington Post&#3;</BODY></TEXT>